In a speech at the National Governors Association, Vice President Mike Pence praised President Trump's commitment to federalism and his partnership with state governors. He highlighted the administration's accomplishments in job creation, energy policy, trade, and infrastructure. Pence also discussed the Senate healthcare bill, emphasizing its benefits such as repealing Obamacare mandates, cutting taxes, and providing more flexibility to states. He acknowledged the concerns about Medicaid, but assured that the bill strengthens and secures the program for the neediest Americans. Pence also mentioned the bill's provisions to address the opioid crisis and urged governors to work together with the administration to improve healthcare and other policies for the American people.